Review Text:
I bought this 1-gang Decora wall plate to finish off a light switch installation, and it’s exactly what I was hoping for. The quality is excellent—sturdy construction with a smooth, glossy finish that looks great on the wall. It fits perfectly over a standard Decora-style switch or outlet and gives everything a clean, modern appearance.

What I really appreciate is the seamless design—no visible screws once it’s installed (depending on the style), and it sits flush against the wall with no gaps or warping. The material feels durable and doesn’t flex or crack like some of the cheaper ones I’ve used in the past.

It’s a small detail, but swapping to a Decora plate really upgraded the look of the room. It matches well with other contemporary hardware and makes everything feel a bit more polished.

If you’re updating switches or outlets, don’t overlook the wall plates—this one is a great choice. Affordable, easy to install, and looks fantastic!

Product Name: 15 Amp 125-Volt Rubber Grounding Plug 515PR-R
Review Title: BEN IN OAK HARBOR IS THE MAN!!!!
Review Text:
Reliable and sturdy. Used to build an inverter-type generator ground bonding plug. Most inverter generators have a “floating neutral”, and if you’re like me and use your inverter generator to power an RV, the surge protector will show an open ground. This can create issues with some appliances inside the RV that think they aren’t getting the right kind of juice. Now in theory, any quality RV’s GFCI *should* detect a non-normal electrical current and trip, however, that isn’t guaranteed. Using this plug and wiring the neutral to ground using 12 gauge wire, the surge protector now sees a true ground and will send the RV all it needs to safely run. 

I’m no electrician, but Ben at the Oak Harbor store is and he has taught me a lot. Thank you, Ben! Great job!

Product Name: Lever Edge 15 Amp 125 Volt Self-Test Tamper-Resistant GFCI Duplex Outlet/Receptacle, White (1-Pack) EGFT1-KW
Review Title: Solid GFCI with a Minor Fit Issue
Review Text:
I recently installed the Leviton Lever Edge GFCI outlet and was generally impressed. The lever-lock connections were a breeze to use, making wiring incredibly fast and easy. The color-coded levers, especially the blue one for the load wire, significantly reduced the chance of miswiring. The self-test and status indicator light are great features, providing peace of mind regarding protection. The build quality feels solid, and the tamper-resistant design is a plus.
However, I deducted a star due to a fit issue with the Decora wall plate compatibility. The tabs at the bottom, designed to accommodate Decora plates, seem to push standard plates slightly away from the wall, creating a noticeable gap. (See attached photos.) No matter what I tried, the plate wouldn't sit flush. This is a bit disappointing, as it detracts from the overall finished look.
Also, while the lever-lock connections are convenient, I have some reservations about their long-term reliability compared to traditional screw terminals. It feels a bit like a trade-off between speed and proven durability. While I appreciate the innovation, I'm a little hesitant to fully trust a new technology without more extensive long-term data. Are we simply too lazy to tighten screws? Perhaps, but screws are a tried and true method. I'm essentially a guinea pig for this new system. I would prefer to wait a few years to see how these tabs hold up before fully endorsing them.
Overall, this is a good GFCI outlet with some excellent features, but the fit issue and the uncertainty surrounding the lever-lock connections prevent it from getting a full five stars.

Product Name: Lever Edge 15 Amp 125 Volt Self-Test Tamper-Resistant GFCI Duplex Outlet/Receptacle, White (1-Pack) EGFT1-KW
Review Text: The item was easy to install. Works as described

Product Name: Lever Edge 15 Amp 125 Volt Self-Test Tamper-Resistant GFCI Duplex Outlet/Receptacle, White (1-Pack) EGFT1-KW
Review Text: Easy install GFCI Receptacle with many additional features. To start, this outlet provides continuous ground-fault protection, ensuring safety by detecting and tripping on actual ground faults even during self-tests. The patented Reset Lockout technology prevents resetting if the GFCI is damaged and unable to respond to a ground fault. But the real game changer for this GFCI receptacle is the lever terminals. These greatly increase the speed of the installation, but more importantly provide added safety, leaving no exposed metal screws thus eliminating the need to rap in electrical tape. The color-coded lever terminals make wiring straightforward and efficient. The unique blue lever for the load wire minimizes the risk of miswiring, and the audible "click" confirms a secure connection. There is even a lever terminal for the ground connection. The outlet includes a status indicator light that provides intuitive feedback on power and protection status, as well as line/load reversal. It also accepts both 12 and 14 wire. The Lever Edge GFCI Outlet is an excellent choice for those prioritizing safety and convenience. In review it has lever terminals that are color coded and have audible connection, a status indicator light, self-test button, and no exposed metal parts. Its innovative design and robust features make it a worthwhile investment for both residential and commercial applications.

Product Name: Lever Edge 15 Amp 125 Volt Self-Test Tamper-Resistant GFCI Duplex Outlet/Receptacle, White (1-Pack) EGFT1-KW
Review Text: The Lever Edge connectors are like back stabs but way, way better. I like that there are no screws on the sides, so there's no chance of shorting to a metal box. Also the direction of the levers means you can't accidentally open one while you push the device into the box. Of course I was skeptical at first, but tugged hard as I could on one of the wires and it wouldn't budge. On back stabs they would pull right out. Watch your fingers though, because the levers have a strong spring that snaps them closed. And it hurts if they snap your fingertip. One thing to note, this GFCI outlet is pretty deep. Make sure your box can handle it.

I'm having to replace all my brand new receptacles in Puerto Rico because the salt air on even the in door receptacles corroded. This USB is a sealed unit and there are no terminals to corrode. The original installed should have used a dielectric grease knowing that this section of the hose with pool was open to the salt air. These Leviton are perfect for this environment.

Product Name: USB Wall Outlet High Power Dual Type-C/C Power Delivery 60W (6A) Charger with 15A Tamper-Resistant Outlet, White T5636-W
Review Text: Good product but a bit expensive.  I also did not see a UL certification and for this money and for a US high end company, I would expect that.  Lastly, as many others have noted, this unit has braided copper wires which need to be attached to the house wiring. There is very little space in the outlet box for this. In older homes, you will likely not get this to fit.

Review Title: Perfect for bathrooms where extra ventilation is needed, or the kids forget to use the fan during a shower
Review Text:
This has been perfect for our needs.  I wanted a bathroom fan switch that would automatically turn on when somebody is showering.  (The kids constantly forget to turn on the fan.)  Also, I've set it up to run for 10 minutes every hour just making sure the room stays ventilated.  It's been great and the bathroom fan is no longer running endlessly as people forget to turn it off at night.

One minor complaint.  I bought this to pair with the Leviton DVS02-1LW vacancy switch to control the lights.  Paired they compliment each other and have similar button feel.  However, they both use a green indicator light but they use it differently.  One has the green light on when switched on, and the other has the green light on when switched off.  It's frustrating and makes the indicator lights less useful.

Product Name: Decora 15 Amp 125 V Duplex Outlet/Receptacle, White (10-Pack) 5325-WMP
Review Text:
I recently upgraded several outlets in my home to these 15-amp decorator-style outlets, and I couldn't be happier with the result. Not only do they function perfectly, but I absolutely love the sleek, modern look of the decorator design. It’s such a simple change, but it really elevates the overall appearance of the room—clean lines and a more contemporary feel compared to the old traditional outlets.

Installation was a breeze, even for a DIYer like me. The terminals were clearly marked, and the build quality is solid. Everything tightened down securely, and the fit into the wall plate was perfect. No gaps or unevenness, just a neat, professional finish.

Performance-wise, the outlet delivers consistent, reliable power. I’ve tested it with various devices—lamps, chargers, small appliances—and everything runs smoothly with no flickering or loose connections. The grip on the plugs is firm, which adds to the overall sense of quality.

If you’re looking to refresh the look of your space while also improving functionality, I highly recommend these 15-amp decorator outlets. They’re a small upgrade that makes a big difference!

Product Name: Decora 15A 60-Minute Indoor In-Wall Countdown Timer Switch 1/2 HP/9.8A Fan/Motor No Neutral Required Single-Pole, White
Review Text: Excellent timer switched that was used to replace a bathroom fan switch.  The install was very simple as there is no need to identity the load/line conductors and no neutral conductor is needed.  The project took 30-minutes in total as I needed to dress the existing conductors in the 3-gang box as to properly seat this switch to be flush like the two other switches.   Note, if you also are installing the switch without a neutral, you will need a larger wire nut than was provided for the original ground conductor plus the two ground leads from the switch.

Product Name: Decora 15A 60-Minute Indoor In-Wall Countdown Timer Switch 1/2 HP/9.8A Fan/Motor No Neutral Required Single-Pole, White
Review Text: We installed these on our new home 8 years ago on all of the bathroom and shower fans. They have worked fantastically well. So when our daughter & husband bought a new home, it was an easy decision to use these again. These are much improved from 8 years ago. The switch body is now shallower making them easy to fit in a crowded box with wire nuts in back. They also are easier to wire up because you no longer have to identify the hot or load wire. Now the black wires are interchangeable!

Product Name: Decora 15A 60-Minute Indoor In-Wall Countdown Timer Switch 1/2 HP/9.8A Fan/Motor No Neutral Required Single-Pole, White
Review Text: I had an Intermatic countdown wall timer installed in 2013 but it finally had issues, cycling through in mere seconds instead of minutes. I wanted the same unit but Home Depot had this one closer to my home. It's great so far. Others have complained about the buttons being cheap and flimsy but it seems to be fine, and the elctronics are behaving as they should. I only just installed it, so we'll see how it is in a few years. Very easy to install. Just cut power first!

Product Name: Decora 15A 60-Minute Indoor In-Wall Countdown Timer Switch 1/2 HP/9.8A Fan/Motor No Neutral Required Single-Pole, White
Review Text: Whenever I move into any house or apartment, I replace the bathroom exhaust fan on/off switch to a timer to make things simple; I have run off to do things or be gone for a couple of days and come back and find the bathroom fan running because it was not checked before leaving the house.  A timer is easy to install and you can set the desired length of time from a few minutes to an hour depending on the needs.

Review Text:
this works great! I just followed the instructions unhook the load wires out of the old switch and disconnected the ground and then attached it all according to the instructions for the new switch. 

I did not have a neutral wire so the ground wire and the neutral wire from the new switch just get attached to your metal ground from your switch box.  
the directions have two types of installs one with neutral wire and one without neutral wire. I did this all in about 10 to 15 minutes. honestly the longest part of it all was getting the wires the load wires out of my old switch that was a little tricky. once I did that you just twist the wires together and put a wire nut over them and shove them back in the switch box and you're done.

Product Name: Decora Lever Edge Rocker Slide Dimmer Switch for LED/INC Bulbs, 150 Watt, Single Pole or 3-Way, White (1-Pack) ESL01-1KW
Review Text: The dimmer switch is the easiest installing switch I've ever used. Instead of having to wrap wire around screws, or even push into hard-to-release slots, you simply place the wire in the hole and shut the individual latches. This makes it SUPER easy to remove/replace in the future. The dimmer also perfectly matches my other Decora styled switches, even though my others are older. I did have to break away the top/bottom tabs to fit my particular setup, but its great they include them for oversize plate covers.

Product Name: Decora Lever Edge Rocker Slide Dimmer Switch for LED/INC Bulbs, 150 Watt, Single Pole or 3-Way, White (1-Pack) ESL01-1KW
Review Title: Hitting Switches Has Never Been Easier!
Review Text:
I've installed many different switches over the years though this was the first with the lever terminals. The installation was made much quicker by not having to mess with the screw on terminals and the levers are labelled to the appropriate wire and keep it very secure. 
The body of the dimmer was not too large and it fit right in my double gang box that I used to replace a non-dimmable switch with this unit. \
Fit and finish are excellent and the installation took less than 20 minutes start to finish- make sure you turn off power to the switch before even thinking about messing with it!

Product Name: Decora Lever Edge Rocker Slide Dimmer Switch for LED/INC Bulbs, 150 Watt, Single Pole or 3-Way, White (1-Pack) ESL01-1KW
Review Text:
This design is replacing the miniscule slider which was uncomfortable and inconvenient to use. It still is, but the cover has a longer slider with a bump in the middle, which provides enough friction to make sliding it easy and intuitive. 
The entire faceplate comes off as on single part, which is the new concept for the Leviton Decora switches - there would be one switch with color matching replaceable plates, instead of different switches. This is where the future concept will be and it is so much better and allows the users to change the color of the switch without changing the entire switch. 
Installation literally takes seconds - the lever design makes it so easy to install and uninstall and repurpose. 
The switches are CSA Certified, UL Listed and fully compliant to all existing NFPA Standards under  NEC 2023.
This switch can be used in single pole or 3-way applications with up to 150Watts of incandescent, CFL or LED lights. 
On a single pole, the dimmer doesn't emit buzzing or flickering and doesn't heat up. Operation and dimming is very gradient, smoot and feels very natural.
This product is made in China, comes with 1-year warranty and is returnable in 90 days.

Product Name: Decora Lever Edge Rocker Slide Dimmer Switch for LED/INC Bulbs, 150 Watt, Single Pole or 3-Way, White (1-Pack) ESL01-1KW
Review Text: Really loved the ease at which you can install this switch. The side flip tabs and push holes in the back are just so much nicer than having to bend the wire and tighten around a screw. This also allows you to save some room in your box by shortening the tails of the wire you cut since you need less clearance on the back of the switch! Once installed, the switch works exactly as expected, the dimming allows you full range of control of the lights (obviously, make sure you're putting this on a circuit with dimming capable lights!), and the slider doesn't interfere with the rocker switch for on/off at all. Didn't install on a 3 way circuit, so I also love that the 3-way connections in the back are clearly labelled and covered with a sticker so you don't accidentally install wrong!

Product Name: Decora Lever Edge Rocker Slide Dimmer Switch for LED/INC Bulbs, 150 Watt, Single Pole or 3-Way, White (1-Pack) ESL01-1KW
Review Title: So simple and quick to install
Review Text: I recently installed the Leviton Decora Lever Edge Rocker Slide Dimmer Switch for our master bath shower light replacing an outdated rotary one that the builder had installed years ago.  It was the easiest switch that I had ever replaced due to the quick and simple push wire connectors.  The color coded clips are also labeled so that there’s no confusion.  They give a firm snap and loud click letting you know that the wire is securely in place.  The factory settings for the dimmer operations were perfect so I didn’t do any further tweaking of the dimming range or fade.

Product Name: Decora Lever Edge Rocker Slide Dimmer Switch for LED/INC Bulbs, 150 Watt, Single Pole or 3-Way, White (1-Pack) ESL01-1KW
Review Text: Easy! So thoughtfully designed. Love the color coding and the secure connector clamps. It literally took me 5 minutes at the most to install. Working with electricity can be intimidating but this product is very straightforward and does a great job in securing wires. Great that the package has installation diagrams and if you need more instruction, there is a QR code on the box that takes you to detailed instructions on the Leviton website. The rocker switch and dimmer slide work great with my LED dimmable ceiling light. I own several Leviton products because they are high quality.

Product Name: Decora Lever Edge Rocker Slide Dimmer Switch for LED/INC Bulbs, 150 Watt, Single Pole or 3-Way, White (1-Pack) ESL01-1KW
Review Text:
It’s an excellent product and it saves a whole lot of time when installing outlets and switches. You know you have a secure, safe connection and it isn’t prone to errors like leaving a screw too loose or hooking the wire the wrong direction. Additionally the sides are plastic so no risk of shock when grabbing the sides.

These lever spring connections are rated beyond what they say they are, and they are safer and are harder to mess up. Absolutely love them, and the time saved.

Review Text: This is exciting!  Push-click-done products have worked great for me.  Switches have worked great!  Receptacles have worked great!  Now make a dimmer!  YAY!  The installation is SO EASY, like the other push-click-done products.  The stock is limited because it is a new product.  So what is the downside: 1) comes only in white 2) comes only in decora style 3) Premium price 4) Scarce.  They are hard to find.  I will be using more of these!

Review Text: I started adding smart switches to our home a couple years ago as we intended to slowly update and renovate our home room by room. A recent accident forced us into a major remodel sooner than planned and I've been adding switches everywhere. However, the path from the first floor to second floor on the stairs isnt as straight forward as it should be so the companion switch is the perfect solution. However, after having this installed for one week, I've had to re-pair it to the main switch 2 times. Im not sure if there is some sort of interference going on with other switches but its quite annoying. For what its worth, I've had to re add every switch in the house at least once. While all of these things are minor inconveniences and easily resolved, it is pretty annoying considering the price. If these types of switches weren't so expensive I'd probably replace them with a different manufacturer.

I replaced the existing switch with a second generation one and placed the wireless anywhere switch at the other end. We are very happy with the results and would recomend this low hassle solution. Lever Edge 15 Amp 125 Volt Self-Test Tamper/Weather Resistant GFCI Duplex Outlet/Receptacle, White (1-Pack) EGFW1-KW
Review Text: This was a fast and easy GFCI receptacle to install, and I would recommend it. I like that it has no exposed terminals so it's safer to use and doesn't require electrical tape around the perimeter to cover the terminals. It has test ports on the side for easy access when needed, and alignment tabs and indents for correct spacing between similar Lever Edge style receptacles. There are a couple of small cons which is why I only gave 4 stars. There are only positions for one set of wires on top and bottom of the receptacle, which requires wire nutting multiple in-coming or out-going wires together and then adding a pig tail for connection to the GFCI. I know this is best practice in most cases, but it's annoying especially when there is limited space in the box. The other issue is that the plastic tabs/ears don't bend as easily which makes adjustments for skewed or out of plumb electrical boxes harder. There are metal pieces behind the plastic, but the plastic resists permanent bending.

Product Name: Lever Edge 15 Amp 125 Volt Self-Test Tamper/Weather Resistant GFCI Duplex Outlet/Receptacle, White (1-Pack) EGFW1-KW
Review Text: Very Easy to Use! Wires are firmly gripped. Ability to capture wires with the push of a lever makes the job much easier. And it is also easy to remove wires when that is required (for example to adjust lengths). One minor problem is removing the extension tab (if required) is difficult because the plastic material doesn’t SNAP off. Rather it is compliant and rubbery and difficult to break off, especially if the unit is already wired into the box.

Product Name: SmartlockPro 15 Amp 125-Volt Self-Test Tamper-Resistant GFCI Outlet with Audible Trip Alert, White GFTA1-KW
Review Title: If it dont work, try this...
Review Text: My old gfci would trip at least twice a week. I replaced it with this unit and at first I couldn't get anything I plugged into it to work. I went to one of those electrical online forums to research why it wouldn't work even though the green led light was lit. The forum suggested that I NOT wiring it exactly how the old one was wired. The forum suggested that Leviton gfcis have different internals. So I tried it and it worked. So dont do a left and right swap but do an up and down swap. Whatever wire was attached to the top brass screw on your old unit, put that same wire on the bottom brass screw on the new unit unit and then do the same thing with the silver screws on the other side. It worked flawlessly for me, maybe for u too, no? Good Luck. That forum saved me an electrician visit...

Product Name: 15 Amp SmartlockPro Wi-Fi Certified Smart GFCI Outlet, White D2GF1-KW
Review Text: Installation instructions were very helpful with identifying Line and Load wires. Take pictures before removing wiring from the old GFCI outlet. Installation could be made easier if the new outlet had simpler wire connections such as plug and click. Otherwise, I would given it a 5 rating. The app works well with the new outlet and sends email notifications when GFCI outlet is tripped and manually reset. Not sure if it will send text notification as I did not have my phone number in the app when I went test that part of the functionality. During setup it does not ask you for your phone number so you will need to go back in the app to add it. Also, just had a firmware update that I had to request to be installed versus having Auto Updates enabled. So again I had to go back into the app and enable Auto Updates. So far I am very satisfied with the product and have a better piece of mind knowing I'll be notified if the circuit trips. I would recommend this product if you have had some wiring experience.

Product Name: 50 Amp 125-Volt/250-Volt EV Charging Single Receptacle/Outlet, Black Heavy-Duty, 1450R-B0
Review Text:
Great upgrade from the normal Leviton Outlet.  The EV version is WAY different.  Much more robust with much more insulation and heavy duty contacts and connections.  

The original non EV rated 14-50 that the previous homeowner installed MELTED and started a small fire in the electrical box.  I was informed that the homeowner grade outlet was not designed to sustain many hours of continuous max amp draw.  

This one is definitely designed for continuous use EV charging.  The only thing that you should be aware of is that the head of the outlet has a bigger diameter than a normal outlet so you will need to buy a faceplate with a larger hole in it.  This will also not fit slimline boxes as the outlet is much deeper than a normal 14/50.

Product Name: 50 Amp 125-Volt/250-Volt EV Charging Single Receptacle/Outlet, Black Heavy-Duty, 1450R-B0
Review Text: I bought this outlet, and a 50 amp GFCI breaker, a deep box and the two necessary wird clamps from HD.    I bought 7 feet of 6/3 Romex cable From a HD competitor that sells Romex by the foot, and also the necessary face plate. Ignore other posts saying that the $9 look alike outlet is OK for EV charging.  This outlet is a very different piece of equipment.  I hired a licensed electrician to do the installation as a side gig.  He said that he was surprised to learn that this product was available at HD since he was used to buying a more expensive EV outlet from an electrical supply house.  He told that in his opinion, the Leviton was as robust as the ones he is used to paying more for.  After a month of use with the GM factory portable charger, the plug never even gets warm..

Product Name: 50 Amp 125-Volt/250-Volt EV Charging Single Receptacle/Outlet, Black Heavy-Duty, 1450R-B0
Review Text: The receptacle looked like it was going to work perfectly.  And it would have but the outdoor box it had to go in was too shallow for the backside of the plug because the wires come in from the back and not the side.   I had to go find another one from another company that you could stab the wires in from the side, which of course costs more.   Otherwise if you’re using this in a metal box indoors, you can buy a deeper box with plenty of backspace to fit the plug in.

Product Name: 50 Amp 125-Volt/250-Volt EV Charging Single Receptacle/Outlet, Black Heavy-Duty, 1450R-B0
Review Text: Great product the only issue I have is that you do not sell a cover for it!  It is a bigger diameter than all the covers you carry, including range receptacle cover.  So why sell a product but not the cover?! Makes no sense!  Sell the cover that fits it and will give it a 5-star rating.  I had to make my own cover from a blank 2-gang cover plate, just wrong!

Product Name: 50 Amp 125-Volt/250-Volt EV Charging Single Receptacle/Outlet, Black Heavy-Duty, 1450R-B0
Review Text: As you install this 14-50 outlet, you immediately recognize how much safer it has to be over the budget Nema 14-50 that it replaced. Just the clamping for the wires is far superior and much more secure. You’ll need an industrial cover plate as the hole is a bit larger to accommodate this outlet.

Product Name: 28 in. Premium Vented Hinged Door, White (for use with 28 in. Structured Media Enclosure) 47605-28S
Review Text:
Leviton products are well designed and made and but a bit pricey.  

We have two structured enclosures, one inside for the modem, router and TV distribution. That's always had a hinged door. The second enclosure is in the garage for the security cameras' POE router with a UPS battery. Started with a non-hinged door figuring I'd never need to open the door. However, we recently had a power failure and the UPS needed to be turned off. Unscrewing the fixed door was less desirable now plus the hinged door now house vents. The cabinet got pretty warm when the summer temps got extreme, so the vents should help. 

Both doors were 28" so it was a easy change out. Wish the enclosure had inserts to accept two screws in the middle section. Only the corners have screw inserts and it would give the door frame more rigidity to have six screws. That's an enclosure issue to could be improved. Perhaps they've already have done it.

Review Title: Highly recommend! Good quality, nice weatherstrip, and room for 12 gauge cords!
Review Text: Highly recommend! I had to replace all my outdoor outlets and covers, I put in EATON WRTR grey receptacles which matched the grey perfectly, it looks like they were made for each other with the fit and color. I’m very happy with the quality, functionality and price! Unlike the other in use covers I tried in this price bracket, the weatherstrip is thick and completely covers the back except for the decora cut out. It is the only one I can comfortably fit both of my 12 gauge cords in while closed and locked, the others could fit maybe one, sometimes none. I like having two round holes for each cord where I can put an insert in one or both holes when not in use, instead of one rectangle where I can’t really fit my cord/s. I can easily see inside and see everything is plugged in properly. It’s plastic so I’m not sure how much locking it will protect it from a thief, but nice to have the childproof latch and lock to prevent someone from accidentally unplugging something important. I think it will last for a long time.

Review Text:
It worked as designed & while I was a bit reluctant of the benefits of having (and buying) the Leviton dual Arc Fault/Ground Fault branch circuit breakers for a home improvement remodel project, they served their purpose and identified a couple open neutrals on some aged 50+ yr old wiring.
They were a bit on the spendy side but are an NEC code requirement for most new construction projects. I’m my case I had a hybrid of old & new so opted to change out all the breakers in my 200amp panel for approximately $1,000 in breakers alone but it’s done and I feel it’s a significant upgrade. I also love how the Leviton breakers are a modular design so changing them out only took a few minutes as there were no wires to undo & reattach, they’re already attached to the bus bars so basically making them plug & play.

Product Name: Decora In-Wall Motion Sensor Light Switch, Motion Activated, Auto-On/Auto-Off, 5-Amp, Single Pole or 3-Way, White
Review Text: This turned out to be a great purchase. We had 3 way switch in our walk-in closet, and this was the best solution to be able to walk in - and not have to toggle the switch. Nice long timer setting, nice defeat switch - handy to douse the light if you don't want it to stay on for the full duration of the timer. The sensor was pretty effective (more on this later), and the other toggle station still functioned normally. Was a bit tricky to wire up (even with 50 years electronic experience), so advise you to read the instructions CAREFULLY, plus make sure that the neutral line is in the box you are planning to use for the install, and given this is a LARGER package, you may have a time getting it all back in safely. Back to the scanner.. too wide a detection range, but found a small tab of tape stuck out to a distance of 1/2" cut that to less than 90 degrees - when placed on the side we didn't want to trigger easily - perfect! Highly recommended - for the price!

Review Title: Leviton double switch is Irritating and questionable operation
Review Text: 1) Toggle operation of these switches is questionable?  Some work very easy and soft and some make a loud stiff click when toggling a few out of the box.  I barely got a year of light use out of the last one before it failed (jammed) and stayed on.  2) Why do they put a tab linking both switches?? You turn 1 switch on and both circuits are on.  You will have to be very careful in breaking off the tab or you're dumb out of luck🤞and you will end up returning it for another.  I got lucky and worked the tab back and forth about 50x before it came loose.   I purchased a double switch to purposely operate 2 separate lights.  Why does Leviton make this so difficult?  I hope I can get more than a year out of this one.

Product Name: Decora Smart Switch Z-Wave 800 Series in White (Neutral Wire Required)
Review Title: New design is both a blessing and a curse
Review Text:
I have previously installed the earlier generation of this switch and this one. This one now doesn't  have any terminal screws or ports to direct connect to from your box. Instead, 4 x small-gauge stranded wires are protruding out of it for which you are expected to make wire splices for each of them. The good part is that you have a bit more flexibility for fitting the oversized switch unit into the box since the connected wires are more flexible and forgiving than the 14 ga wites in the wall.

The bad however: hope you folks don't mind using wire nuts over lever nuts (WAGOs) or push-in connectors. All the extra splice connections in combo with the size of this switch does not leave room to use WAGOs, and the stranded wire (if you are selling this in North America Leviton, please stick with solid wire and save us the headaches) won't go into a push-in connector.

The installation aside, the switch works well and does what it is meant to do. I am planning to hook it into my security alarm's home automation system right away.

Two last tips:

1) if this isn't a sqap for an existing switch and you have the luxury of installing a new box, pay extra for the 3"deep (15 cu in volume per device) box. You will appreciate the extra space with this guy.

2) I found out the hard way that if you hook the thing up and the light is always on no matter what you press on the switch, it means you likely lost your neutral splice and need to re-check that connection. Moreover, if splicing the switch white wire to a bundle of multiple neutral wires, I suggest you strip it back an extra 30-50% from what it already is in order to get a good twist and good connection.

Review Title: Power cut in half when two cables are plugged in
Review Text:
I bought this outlet partly so I could stop using the bulky 67W charger from Apple, but mostly so that I could stop having to swap cables so often, between my watch charger and MagSafe laptop cable.

If I have just the MagSafe cable plugged in, my laptop reports it gets 60W. If a lightning cable is plugged into the 2nd port, the laptop reports only 30W -- even if nothing is connected to the lightning cable!

There goes half the reason I bought this thing. I have to unplug my watch charger in order to get 60W for my laptop, and then plug the watch charger back in when I want to use it.

Aside from that, I would have preferred terminals to attach household wiring too, not stranded wires taking up more room in the electrical box when the outlet itself is so large.

Don’t bother wasting your time going to a store as you will just need to go to an electrical supply to get the faceplate anyway. Look at some of the dodgy install photos in these reviews to see what I mean.  Very dangerous and irresponsible.

Review Text: Great value.I didn't have the issues described by the other reviewer. Worked with the non-Leviton keystones that I bought online.

Product Name: PVC Plug 3-Wire, Yellow
Review Text: Good quality plug. Factory assembly is loose so the screws jingle inside, but once tightened it is fine. Made in Mexico.

Product Name: Cartridge Fuse 30 Amp
Review Text: Apparently there are different sizes of fuse that look exactly the same, except for their size. They seem to have the same number code and as far as I can tell every searchable thing is exactly the same, except one (The one I ordered) is like pinky finger sized, and another (the one I actually NEEDED) is about twice as big and wide. So obviously I wasted my money because what I got wouldn't fit. For all I know there are other sizes, too. If I actually went to a store I could take the old fuse with me and make sure it was right, but online there's no sense of scale. What would really help, is if the serial number on an item like this actually DISTINGUISHED the product you are looking for, but since it doesn't, I do not recommend ordering online.

Review Text: I used it as an inexpensive EV charger inside a weatherproof box outside the house.

Product Name: Decora SureSlide Single Pole Universal Slide-Off Dimmer Switch in White (5-Pack)
Review Text: These dimmers are a very low quality product and they don't even work properly.  As you slide the dimmer from the max position, they appear to work properly; however, as you get closer to the min position, they actually stop working and no longer dim the lights.

Product Name: Decora Vizia 24-hour programmable timer, (2-Pack)
Review Title: Great timers that do everything automatically!
Review Text: Great outdoor light timers that turn on when it gets dark.  You have the flexibility to leave them on till sunrise or set the timer to turn them off at a certain hour (eg 11:00 pm). They also automatically adjust for daylight savings time. They have a battery backup so power failures don’t mean you go back to square one setting them up again.
